condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A (d) | Description :The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain at all timesthrough the Project implementation period, a Regional Procurement Evaluation Committee with powers satisfactory to the Association| Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.A (a) | Description: The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain at all timesthrough the Project implementation period a Program Steering Committee. | Frequency: Monthly
Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.A (b) | Description: The Recipient shall nominate a representative to the Program SteeringCommittee | Frequency: Monthly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.A (c) | Description: The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain at all timesthrough the Project implementation period a National Steering Committee with powers and composition satisfactory to the Association| Frequency: Monthly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.A (e) | Description: The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain throughout theProject implementation period, the Project Support Team with powers and composition satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency:Monthly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.C.1 | Description: The Recipient shall adopt and thereafter carry out the project inaccordance with an Operations Manual satisfactory to the Association | Frequency: Monthly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.F | Description: The Recipient shall collect from departing international passengers aAUD5 equivalent levy for use to pay aviation safety and security expenditures | Due Date :30-Jun-2014

Schedule 2, Section E.4 (a): The Recipient shall ensure that all solid waste generated by Project activities shall be disposed ofin accordance with acceptable environmental practices as further stipulated in the EMP.

Schedule 2, Section E.4 (b): Without limitation on the foregoing, if any activity proposed for inclusion in Part 1 of the Projectwould require the export of Project waste outside the territory of the Recipient, the recipient shall ensure that no such exportshall commence until and unless: (i) all measures required to be taken under said EMP prior to the commencement of said activitieshave been taken; and (ii) the Association has confirmed that said activities may be commenced.
The Recipient shall maintain, until December 31, 2019, a Service Agreement with TAL, with terms and conditions satisfactory to theAssociation.
